                            <comment id="13050274" author="tcn" created="Thu, 16 Jun 2011 08:09:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fix is easy:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;$ cat /tmp/json &lt;br/&gt;
{&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;74657374&quot;: [[&quot;data&quot;, &quot;&lt;/p&gt;
{\&quot;foo\&quot;:\&quot;bar\&quot;}
&lt;p&gt;&quot;, 1308209845388000]]&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;$ ./json2sstable -s -c transactions -K foo /tmp/json /var/lib/cassandra/data/foo/transactions-g-1-Data.db&lt;br/&gt;
Counting keys to import, please wait... (NOTE: to skip this use -n &amp;lt;num_keys&amp;gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
Importing 1 keys...&lt;br/&gt;
1 keys imported successfully.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;default@foo&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; get transactions&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;test&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;data&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;;&lt;br/&gt;
=&amp;gt; (column=data, value=&lt;/p&gt;
{&quot;foo&quot;:&quot;bar&quot;}
&lt;p&gt;, timestamp=1308209845388000)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13050693" author="brandon.williams" created="Thu, 16 Jun 2011 20:04:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13050809" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 16 Jun 2011 23:38:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Tatu&apos;s feedback:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The best way to handle escaping/quoting is to use tools that deal with the format &amp;#8211; this patch only handles escaping of double-quotes, but similar problems would occur with linefeeds, or backslashes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So using a JSON generator / writer would make sense, if project uses one already? If not, I would recommend adding handling of backslashes and white space other than space (char codes below 32), as those must be escaped in String values and keys.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also: if unquoted keys were required (not valid JSON, but there&apos;s lots of data like that...), Jackson can be configured to accept unquoted field names. That has its own potential issues (whether escaping is allowed, which characters are legal in unquotes names), but appears to work well enough that users haven&apos;t complained.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13050811" author="brandon.williams" created="Thu, 16 Jun 2011 23:42:51 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So using a JSON generator / writer would make sense, if project uses one already? If not, I would recommend adding handling of backslashes and white space other than space (char codes below 32), as those must be escaped in String values and keys.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We don&apos;t use one.  I believe the historical reason is that one couldn&apos;t be found that would handle things incrementally, but I think that may have changed by now (sst2j is pretty long in the tooth) and we should probably switch to one if possible.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13050863" author="hudson" created="Fri, 17 Jun 2011 02:20:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Cassandra-0.8 #173 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/Cassandra-0.8/173/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/Cassandra-0.8/173/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    sstable2json escapes quotes.&lt;br/&gt;
Patch by Pavel Yaskevich, reviewed by brandonwilliams for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-2780&quot; title=&quot;sstable2json needs to escape quotes&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-2780&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-2780&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;brandonwilliams : &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/viewcvs.cgi/?root=Apache-SVN&amp;amp;view=rev&amp;amp;rev=1136637&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/viewcvs.cgi/?root=Apache-SVN&amp;amp;view=rev&amp;amp;rev=1136637&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Files : &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;/cassandra/branches/cassandra-0.8/test/unit/org/apache/cassandra/SchemaLoader.java&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;/cassandra/branches/cassandra-0.8/src/java/org/apache/cassandra/tools/SSTableExport.java&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;/cassandra/branches/cassandra-0.8/test/unit/org/apache/cassandra/tools/SSTableExportTest.java&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13050923" author="tcn" created="Fri, 17 Jun 2011 08:03:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch will replace existing \&quot; with &lt;br class=&quot;atl-forced-newline&quot; /&gt;&quot; (backslash backslash quote) which may not be the desired behaviour.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Alternative (regex should be precompiled, of course):&lt;br/&gt;
String.format(&quot;\&quot;%s\&quot;&quot;, val.replaceAll(&quot;(?&amp;lt;!\\\\)\&quot;&quot;, &quot;\\\\\&quot;&quot;));&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13050948" author="xedin" created="Fri, 17 Jun 2011 09:47:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;changed replace with pattern/matcher with your regex in the escapeQuotes method. thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13051109" author="tcn" created="Fri, 17 Jun 2011 14:51:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;D&apos;oh, actually an existing \&quot; must be replaced with \\\&quot; :-\&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13051117" author="xedin" created="Fri, 17 Jun 2011 14:56:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you please post a correct regex so i can include it to patch?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13051124" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 17 Jun 2011 15:08:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Why are we talking about regexes instead of taking Tatu&apos;s advice?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13051126" author="xedin" created="Fri, 17 Jun 2011 15:13:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Agreed, I see now that would be the best option. Will be working at that direction.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13051245" author="xedin" created="Fri, 17 Jun 2011 18:48:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;uses ObjectMapper.writeValue(PrintStream, Object) to serialize keys and columns to JSON instead of using regexs.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13051270" author="brandon.williams" created="Fri, 17 Jun 2011 19:20:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed v2, thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13051311" author="hudson" created="Fri, 17 Jun 2011 20:27:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Cassandra-0.8 #175 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/Cassandra-0.8/175/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/Cassandra-0.8/175/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    Use jackson&apos;s ObjectMapper instead of hand-crafting json in sstable2json.&lt;br/&gt;
Patch by Pavel Yaskevich, reviewed by brandonwilliams for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-2780&quot; title=&quot;sstable2json needs to escape quotes&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-2780&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-2780&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;brandonwilliams : &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/viewcvs.cgi/?root=Apache-SVN&amp;amp;view=rev&amp;amp;rev=1136991&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/viewcvs.cgi/?root=Apache-SVN&amp;amp;view=rev&amp;amp;rev=1136991&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Files : &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;/cassandra/branches/cassandra-0.8/src/java/org/apache/cassandra/tools/SSTableExport.java&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13051896" author="tcn" created="Mon, 20 Jun 2011 10:08:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sure, using a real serializer is always better (but usually somewhat slower). Works nicely. Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
